WEBVTT

00:02.710 --> 00:04.460
Previously on "Kevin (Probably)
Saves the World"...

00:04.460 --> 00:05.420
-I'm a messenger from God.
-Oh, good.

00:05.420 --> 00:07.040
I'm here to guide
and protect you.

00:07.040 --> 00:08.380
Who are you talking to?

00:08.380 --> 00:09.620
She can't see me.

00:09.620 --> 00:11.710
The only job you have
in life is to build up

00:11.710 --> 00:13.920
your spiritual powers
through acts of kindness

00:13.920 --> 00:15.290
and selflessness.
[ Laughs ]

00:15.290 --> 00:17.500
God is gonna show you how
to find the other righteous.

00:17.500 --> 00:19.580
Can you please explain to me
why I can't tell anyone

00:19.580 --> 00:22.080
who I am, who you are,
or what I'm doing?

00:22.080 --> 00:23.750
When are you gonna
ask Amy out?

00:23.750 --> 00:24.710
What do you think?

00:24.710 --> 00:26.830
No.

00:26.830 --> 00:29.670
If you were to ask me out,
I would say yes.

00:29.670 --> 00:31.330
You and the others still need
to find out what happened

00:31.330 --> 00:33.040
to the other 35 righteous.

00:33.040 --> 00:35.540
-Sweet murder board.
-Aah!

00:35.540 --> 00:37.000
-He's one of you?!
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:37.000 --> 00:38.210
Big time.
That's why I'm here.

00:38.210 --> 00:39.420
I want to join Team Kevin.

00:39.420 --> 00:40.580
No. No.
Great!

00:40.580 --> 00:42.000
-Team Kevin forever, right?
-[ Laughs ]

00:42.000 --> 00:43.750
I have
a mission for you.

00:46.290 --> 00:48.080
Oh, look at them.

00:48.080 --> 00:51.290
Brought together by
the whims of happenstance.

00:51.290 --> 00:54.380
Random moments
connecting their lives.

00:54.380 --> 00:56.540
It takes my breath away
to think about

00:56.540 --> 01:00.420
how you are
screwing it all up for them!

01:00.420 --> 01:01.960
[ Quietly ]
I'm going as fast as I can.

01:01.960 --> 01:03.920
Seems like you're afraid
of a little dirt, Kevin.

01:03.920 --> 01:05.580
[ Groans ]
I wish this was dirt.

01:05.580 --> 01:08.540
The clock is ticking, Kevin.
Tick-tock, tick-tock.

01:08.540 --> 01:09.540
Everything okay
down there?

01:09.540 --> 01:11.920
You bet!

01:11.920 --> 01:14.710
Oh. Smooth sailing.

01:14.710 --> 01:17.000
Oh!

01:17.000 --> 01:18.790
Found it!

01:18.790 --> 01:20.170
[ Groans ]

01:22.120 --> 01:23.670
Okay, he's down on one knee.

01:23.670 --> 01:25.830
Oh, they're laughing, they're
laughing, they're laughing!

01:25.830 --> 01:28.330
Ooh, she said yes!
She said yes!

01:28.330 --> 01:30.500
She said yes!

01:30.500 --> 01:32.460
[ Laughs ]

01:34.790 --> 01:37.830
You guys
seem familiar.

01:37.830 --> 01:39.790
Kevin? Are you okay?

01:39.790 --> 01:40.830
Kevin?

01:40.830 --> 01:41.580
[ Rat screeches ]
Ohh!

01:41.580 --> 01:42.460
[ Splash ]

01:46.790 --> 01:48.380
[ Scrubbing ]

01:50.080 --> 01:52.080
You do realize that tomato juice
is supposed to be

01:52.080 --> 01:53.710
for skunks, right?

01:53.710 --> 01:55.920
I'll have you know there was
a dead skunk in the sewer,

01:55.920 --> 01:58.210
so who feels like
the stupid one now?

01:58.210 --> 02:01.580
What makes you think they were
the exact same butterflies?

02:01.580 --> 02:04.330
I'm telling you, new vision,
same as the old vision.

02:04.330 --> 02:06.250
I mean, what reason
would the Universe have

02:06.250 --> 02:08.170
for sending
a repeat vision?

02:08.170 --> 02:09.710
[ Gasps ]
We should ask Dave.

02:09.710 --> 02:11.830
Like I said, Dave
will be gone for a while.

02:11.830 --> 02:13.210
A "Secret Mission," I know.

02:13.210 --> 02:16.620
I just think as
captain of Team Kevin --

02:16.620 --> 02:18.880
Coach, then.

02:18.880 --> 02:21.960
I'm Kevin.

02:21.960 --> 02:24.710
Look, I just want to know
where all of our players are

02:24.710 --> 02:25.830
at all times.

02:25.830 --> 02:28.540
[ Sighs ] Focus, please.

02:28.540 --> 02:32.120
Now, the first time you saw
the butterflies was...?

02:32.120 --> 02:34.540
In my room,
after helping Reese.

02:34.540 --> 02:36.750
So, perhaps there's
a connection.

02:38.500 --> 02:41.250
Maybe the Universe is trying
to get you to go back.

02:41.250 --> 02:42.750
To my room.

02:42.750 --> 02:43.960
To Reese.

02:43.960 --> 02:45.080
[ Gasps ]

02:45.080 --> 02:46.710
Yes. Right.

02:46.710 --> 02:48.620
Yep, that --

02:48.620 --> 02:53.960
♪♪

02:53.960 --> 02:55.170
That does make more sense,

02:55.170 --> 02:58.290
'cause I have been
in my room quite a lot.

02:58.290 --> 03:00.710
Friend problems?

03:00.710 --> 03:01.830
Someone
"Mean Girl"-ing you?

03:01.830 --> 03:03.040
No.

03:03.040 --> 03:05.040
Schoolwork?
Troubled romance?

03:05.040 --> 03:07.880
No.
[ Sighs ]

03:07.880 --> 03:09.620
Puberty?

03:09.620 --> 03:12.250
Mm! No.

03:12.250 --> 03:14.040
School teachers?

03:14.040 --> 03:16.210
[ Gasps ]
Oh, they play!

03:16.210 --> 03:17.920
What about the play?

03:17.920 --> 03:19.670
What about the play?

03:19.670 --> 03:21.920
It's your big theatrical debut.
You must be nervous.

03:21.920 --> 03:23.330
I can help.
I told you,

03:23.330 --> 03:26.380
I'm not in the play,
I'm on the stage crew.

03:26.380 --> 03:29.710
Reese, there are
no small parts.

03:29.710 --> 03:31.330
Only small people.

03:31.330 --> 03:32.380
[ Scoffs ]
You're an idiot.

03:32.380 --> 03:33.500
What?

03:33.500 --> 03:34.670
You don't even
need to go.

03:34.670 --> 03:37.170
I am definitely
going to your play.

03:37.170 --> 03:39.120
No doubt, okay?
Hey, um,

03:39.120 --> 03:41.290
can I talk to you guys
for a minute?

03:41.290 --> 03:43.710
Sure. I'm just helping Reese
get over her stage fright.

03:43.710 --> 03:46.120
Um, okay.

03:46.120 --> 03:47.540
I have to
tell you something.

03:47.540 --> 03:48.710
Mm-hmm.

03:48.710 --> 03:50.380
And it's kind of
a big deal.

03:50.380 --> 03:52.040
Mm-hmm.
Okay?

03:53.580 --> 03:56.250
I'm going out on a date.

03:56.250 --> 03:57.620
And I want you to know
that I'm not trying

03:57.620 --> 03:59.960
to replace your father.

03:59.960 --> 04:01.830
Okay.
Okay.

04:01.830 --> 04:05.170
Yeah, he's a co-worker from
school, he's really nice.

04:05.170 --> 04:06.420
His name's Iggy.

04:06.420 --> 04:07.920
Is he a character from
a children's cartoon?

04:07.920 --> 04:09.330
[ Snickers ]

04:09.330 --> 04:10.830
It's short for Ignacio.

04:10.830 --> 04:12.540
Okay. Actually, that's
a pretty cool name.

04:12.540 --> 04:14.250
Yeah, well, he's
a pretty cool guy.
It is.

04:14.250 --> 04:17.540
He teaches philosophy
and theology.

04:17.540 --> 04:19.380
Nope, sorry,
he's back to uncool.

04:19.380 --> 04:21.330
Okay, you know what,
I am anxious enough already

04:21.330 --> 04:22.790
without a bunch of heckling
from the peanut gallery.

04:22.790 --> 04:24.790
Okay, I'm sorry.
I am sorry.

04:24.790 --> 04:26.620
Here I come. I'm making
everything better.

04:26.620 --> 04:28.380
[ Sighs ]
Come on. I'm sorry. Come here.

04:28.380 --> 04:30.170
I think it's fabulous
that you're dating again.

04:30.170 --> 04:33.080
And, Reese,
also, don't you think

04:33.080 --> 04:37.500
it's fabulous that your mom
feels ready to date again?

04:37.500 --> 04:40.290
Reese?

04:40.290 --> 04:41.420
Okay.
I --

04:41.420 --> 04:42.960
You know what?

04:42.960 --> 04:44.750
I don't know why
I bother with you two.

04:44.750 --> 04:46.460
I don't.
I --

04:46.460 --> 04:48.790
[ Sighs ]

04:51.170 --> 04:56.000
Do you need me to help
process this news?

04:56.000 --> 04:58.290
Must be pretty upsetting.

04:58.290 --> 05:02.250
♪♪

05:02.250 --> 05:04.250
Kev, can't
thank you enough

05:04.250 --> 05:05.790
for the assist
on this little minx.

05:05.790 --> 05:07.120
Any time, man.

05:07.120 --> 05:08.960
Took me 12 long years
to track her down,

05:08.960 --> 05:11.000
but now she's finally mine.

05:11.960 --> 05:16.960
12 years? Is this some
kind of special papasan?

05:16.960 --> 05:21.710
Why yes, Kevin.
Yes, it is.

05:21.710 --> 05:23.460
I was 15 years old.

05:23.460 --> 05:25.040
The Kautter Family basement.

05:25.040 --> 05:27.830
And this rattan-framed
beauty cradled me

05:27.830 --> 05:30.500
during in my first kiss.

05:30.500 --> 05:32.920
That's, uh...sweet.

05:32.920 --> 05:35.040
Yeah, I thought so, too.

05:35.040 --> 05:36.960
Mrs. Kautter was
a little creeped out.

05:36.960 --> 05:38.790
But she eventually
sold it to me.

05:38.790 --> 05:42.000
And, I got to say...

05:42.000 --> 05:44.120
totally worth the wait.

05:47.920 --> 05:51.000
I'll give you a moment.
[ Sighs ]

05:51.000 --> 05:53.670
[ Birds chirping ]

05:53.670 --> 06:00.620
♪♪

06:00.620 --> 06:02.000
Hey, Ty?

06:02.000 --> 06:05.210
Do you see
a-a butterfly?

06:05.210 --> 06:06.670
Are you the butterfly?

06:06.670 --> 06:07.750
I don't think so.

06:07.750 --> 06:11.580
Then my answer is no.

06:11.580 --> 06:15.330
How would you feel about
taking a little detour home?

06:15.330 --> 06:22.670
♪♪

06:22.670 --> 06:25.210
[ Horns honking ]

06:25.210 --> 06:35.120
♪♪

06:35.120 --> 06:37.750
Oh, okay.
Reese's school.

06:37.750 --> 06:42.380
♪♪

06:42.380 --> 06:44.960
Whoa.
Sorry, guys. Wrong class.

06:44.960 --> 06:49.790
Uh, nope. I-I-I think this is,
uh -- I think this is us.

06:49.790 --> 06:52.920
You're taking my continuing
education art class for seniors?

06:52.920 --> 06:57.080
Well, we're more like,
uh, auditing it.

06:57.080 --> 06:58.580
Check with
the learning center.

06:58.580 --> 06:59.880
Classes within
your age range

06:59.880 --> 07:01.380
start at the beginning
of each month.

07:01.380 --> 07:02.880
Are you sure
you don't need any help

07:02.880 --> 07:04.420
[chuckles ]
with the class?

07:04.420 --> 07:08.830
Just cleaning brushes,
sharpening pencils, anything?

07:08.830 --> 07:12.330
I am in a bit of a jam.

07:12.330 --> 07:15.170
How comfortable are you
with your body?

07:16.710 --> 07:25.710
♪♪

07:25.710 --> 07:27.250
[ Clears throat ]

07:27.250 --> 07:29.750
♪♪

07:29.750 --> 07:31.750
Great line weight, Cheryl.

07:31.750 --> 07:34.710
Very loose and balanced.

07:34.710 --> 07:36.580
Hey. Hello, ma'am?

07:36.580 --> 07:39.540
Sorry, could you please
not distract my students?

07:39.540 --> 07:41.920
Sorry.

07:41.920 --> 07:43.120
Try experimenting...

07:43.120 --> 07:45.040
How do you
stay so still?

07:45.040 --> 07:47.250
As a kid, I'd spend hours
in front of store windows,

07:47.250 --> 07:50.170
pretending I was a mannequin
while my mom went shopping.

07:50.170 --> 07:52.620
One day she left me there
overnight. So much fun.

07:52.620 --> 07:54.830
[ Laughs ]

07:54.830 --> 07:57.000
[ Wind whistling ]

07:57.000 --> 08:01.500
♪♪

08:01.500 --> 08:03.210
Okay, you know what?

08:03.210 --> 08:05.670
Turns out I only need
one gladiator after all.

08:05.670 --> 08:07.250
One gladiator's good.
You can leave.

08:07.250 --> 08:09.170
No, I'm sorry.
I just -- I'm sorry.

08:09.170 --> 08:11.120
-Shield.
-See you in the car, K-Dog!

08:11.120 --> 08:13.920
-Okay.
-Come on. Shield. Shield.

08:13.920 --> 08:15.540
Let's go.
[ Gasps ]

08:15.540 --> 08:17.080
Wait, wait, wait.

08:17.080 --> 08:19.830
I promise I'll be so good.
One more chance. I'll be quiet.

08:19.830 --> 08:22.790
Please, please, please.
I'll be so, so quiet.

08:22.790 --> 08:25.000
Never quieter. The quietest.
All right. All right.

08:25.000 --> 08:26.670
[ Softly ] Sorry.

08:26.670 --> 08:29.040
♪♪

08:29.040 --> 08:30.920
Eyebrows over there
is a freaking natural.

08:30.920 --> 08:32.250
What are you doing here?

08:32.250 --> 08:33.540
I gave you a mission.

08:33.540 --> 08:34.750
I know.

08:34.750 --> 08:36.210
And I failed.

08:36.210 --> 08:37.710
Hard.

08:42.120 --> 08:43.710
I talked to
every one of us.

08:43.710 --> 08:45.710
I gave my best sales pitch,
you know, "Rejoin the cause!

08:45.710 --> 08:48.920
Help save the world. Maybe get
a new soul to protect."

08:48.920 --> 08:50.290
And they all said
the same thing?

08:50.290 --> 08:51.580
A big, fat, juicy nope.

08:51.580 --> 08:54.620
Even Ava?

08:54.620 --> 08:56.620
Especially Ava.

08:56.620 --> 08:59.790
She said she wanted
nothing to do with you.

08:59.790 --> 09:01.540
Hey.

09:01.540 --> 09:03.120
Hey.

09:03.120 --> 09:04.710
Come on.
We'll get through this.

09:04.710 --> 09:05.670
All right?

09:05.670 --> 09:06.830
Look, I know
how these kids feel.

09:06.830 --> 09:07.880
I've been there myself.

09:07.880 --> 09:09.960
Just let them
burn through all that anger

09:09.960 --> 09:13.330
and resentment while
we focus our energy on Kevin.

09:13.330 --> 09:15.170
As soon as he anoints
a new righteous,

09:15.170 --> 09:17.040
the rest'll come around.
Trust me.

09:17.040 --> 09:18.750
[ Sighs ]

09:18.750 --> 09:19.620
You think so?

09:19.620 --> 09:21.960
You bet your
sweet ass I do.

09:21.960 --> 09:24.670
We're not there yet.
Duly noted.

09:24.670 --> 09:28.790
Hey! I wanted
to return your costume.

09:28.790 --> 09:31.420
Sorry. There you go.

09:31.420 --> 09:34.790
Um, sorry if I was
too disruptive in class.

09:34.790 --> 09:37.000
Not your fault.
It's me.

09:37.000 --> 09:39.580
I've been in a snit all day.

09:39.580 --> 09:41.210
Is something bugging you?

09:44.880 --> 09:47.040
What do you think
about this?

09:47.040 --> 09:50.670
[ Chuckles ] I think it's
really good. Is that yours?

09:50.670 --> 09:52.540
Yeah.

09:52.540 --> 09:56.210
So, how come all your great art
is just piled up in this car?

09:56.210 --> 09:59.000
Supposed to be part of
an art exhibit this weekend.

09:59.000 --> 10:00.790
My first.

10:00.790 --> 10:03.540
Friends own a gallery in Austin,
asked me to be a part of it.

10:03.540 --> 10:05.620
[ Car door closes ]
What happened?

10:05.620 --> 10:09.460
Same thing as always --
I book a show, get psyched,

10:09.460 --> 10:10.960
but when the moment comes,

10:10.960 --> 10:13.880
I -- I can't bring
myself to do it.

10:13.880 --> 10:16.210
Gotten to a point I just
keep them in the car now,

10:16.210 --> 10:18.120
hoping to build up
enough courage.

10:18.120 --> 10:19.420
Well, what
are you afraid of?

10:19.420 --> 10:22.170
I mean, what's the worst
that could happen?

10:22.170 --> 10:24.250
Everyone says that I suck.

10:24.250 --> 10:26.830
Uh, well, people tell me
that I suck,

10:26.830 --> 10:28.920
literally, every day,
and it's not that bad.

10:28.920 --> 10:30.460
I'm a coward.

10:30.460 --> 10:32.620
Better to be left
wondering than mortified.

10:32.620 --> 10:34.750
Excuse me.
Well...[ Sighs ]

10:34.750 --> 10:38.170
Okay.
[ Engine starts ]

10:38.750 --> 10:41.210
♪♪

10:41.210 --> 10:42.580
[ Knocking on window ]

10:42.580 --> 10:43.750
Sorry.

10:43.750 --> 10:45.170
What are you doing?

10:45.170 --> 10:47.420
I am looking at a guy
who's clearly talented,

10:47.420 --> 10:48.620
but needs assistance.

10:48.620 --> 10:50.120
And how do you know that?

10:50.120 --> 10:53.880
Because I am a patron
of the arts.

10:53.880 --> 10:57.040
I love all the great
artists, artworks --

10:57.040 --> 11:00.250
Mona Lisa, um, Soup Can,

11:00.250 --> 11:02.710
People At The Park
Made Our of Dots,

11:02.710 --> 11:06.880
um, Screamy Face,
Melty Clocks -- personal fave.

11:06.880 --> 11:09.290
Very impressive.
But I'm -- I'm not --

11:09.290 --> 11:11.620
Look, look, look, you can
barely fit in your car.

11:11.620 --> 11:13.210
I have a truck.
I'll drive you to Austin.

11:13.210 --> 11:14.540
I can help set up.

11:14.540 --> 11:16.330
I'll -- I'll -- I'll
cheer you on.

11:16.330 --> 11:18.210
You're not gonna let go
until I say yes, are you?

11:18.210 --> 11:20.120
Pretty much, yeah.

11:20.120 --> 11:22.750
All right. Fine.
I-I'll do it.

11:22.750 --> 11:24.960
Yes! You will not
regret this.

11:24.960 --> 11:27.500
Now please let go.
Sorry.

11:31.120 --> 11:32.670
-Oh, hey.
-Hi.

11:32.670 --> 11:34.040
-Sorry.
-No. I-I'm sorry.

11:34.040 --> 11:36.080
Uh, were you
leaving or...?

11:36.080 --> 11:38.620
No. I mean, yeah,
I w-- I was leaving,

11:38.620 --> 11:40.790
but, um,
I-I can talk if...

11:40.790 --> 11:41.580
Are you here to talk?

11:41.580 --> 11:44.080
Uh, yes, I --

11:44.080 --> 11:45.750
Well, I actually just

11:45.750 --> 11:48.330
wanted to see if
you've given any thought to,

11:48.330 --> 11:51.170
uh -- to tomorrow night?

11:51.170 --> 11:54.120
Definitely. Yeah.
Like, so many thoughts.

11:54.120 --> 11:55.670
That's great.

11:55.670 --> 11:56.750
Yeah.
Yeah.

11:56.750 --> 11:58.620
Well, I-I know you have
the play first,

11:58.620 --> 12:01.580
but I'm flexible for whatever
you want to do after.

12:01.580 --> 12:04.750
Oh, sure.
Like, um, dinner?

12:04.750 --> 12:06.380
I'm open to anything.

12:06.380 --> 12:08.250
Or we could go to
a movie, you know?

12:08.250 --> 12:09.620
Uh, but I will have
just been sitting

12:09.620 --> 12:10.960
for a couple of hours,
so, you know,

12:10.960 --> 12:12.380
something active
may be nice.

12:12.380 --> 12:13.830
[ Chuckles ]

12:13.830 --> 12:15.500
But not too active.

12:15.500 --> 12:19.000
Like a museum, you know,
or dancing or mini-golf.

12:19.000 --> 12:21.710
How about
that last one? Hmm?

12:21.710 --> 12:22.620
Mini -- Mini-golf?

12:22.620 --> 12:23.880
Fantastic.

12:23.880 --> 12:25.330
Yeah, haven't
done it in years.

12:25.330 --> 12:26.420
Should I meet you there?

12:26.420 --> 12:29.210
Yeah. Yeah, sure.
That'll be great.

12:29.210 --> 12:31.420
Oh. Great.

12:32.960 --> 12:34.120
Mini-golf?

12:34.120 --> 12:36.880
Amy. Mini-golf?

12:36.880 --> 12:38.380
[ Crickets chirping ]

12:41.790 --> 12:44.000
Ah! Who wants to check out
an ultra-hip

12:44.000 --> 12:46.120
Austin art show with me?

12:46.120 --> 12:48.750
Since when are you
into art?

12:48.750 --> 12:51.120
I'm not. But you are.

12:51.120 --> 12:53.620
Figured you could
be my ringer.

12:53.620 --> 12:54.580
When is it?

12:54.580 --> 12:56.830
Tomorrow.

12:56.830 --> 12:58.790
You forgot.

12:58.790 --> 13:00.210
Forgot what?

13:00.210 --> 13:02.500
My school play.
It's tomorrow.

13:06.250 --> 13:08.000
Uh...

13:08.000 --> 13:11.290
Oh, man, you totally
fell for it --

13:11.290 --> 13:14.040
"Kevin, you forgot
my school play."

13:14.040 --> 13:15.420
Totally fooled you.

13:15.420 --> 13:18.880
That is hilarious.
You are too easy, kiddo.

13:18.880 --> 13:21.460
Mm-hmm.
Too easy.

13:21.460 --> 13:23.750
If you have something
else to do, I get it.

13:23.750 --> 13:25.880
It's...not a big deal.

13:25.880 --> 13:27.790
What? No. That is silly.

13:27.790 --> 13:32.080
I am definitely gonna...

13:32.080 --> 13:33.210
be there. Uh...

13:33.210 --> 13:35.460
Seriously,
it's not a big deal.

13:35.460 --> 13:37.580
I told you
you didn't have to go.

13:37.580 --> 13:39.250
Really?

13:41.920 --> 13:44.210
Oh, hey, guys.

13:44.210 --> 13:45.120
[ Door closes ]

13:45.120 --> 13:46.830
Guys? Dave!

13:46.830 --> 13:47.880
Hey there, handsome.

13:47.880 --> 13:49.080
When did you get back?

13:49.080 --> 13:52.960
Uh, earlier today.
And I'm leaving.

13:54.040 --> 13:55.210
You are?

13:55.210 --> 13:56.540
Just for a few days.

13:56.540 --> 13:58.540
I need to
recharge my batteries.

13:58.540 --> 14:01.620
Dave here will keep an eye
on you while I'm gone.

14:01.620 --> 14:03.540
Are you comfortable
with that, Dave?

14:03.540 --> 14:05.080
Are you kidding?

14:05.080 --> 14:06.380
[ Buttons pop ]

14:06.380 --> 14:07.750
I've been waiting
for this moment.

14:07.750 --> 14:10.000
"Team Kev--"

14:10.000 --> 14:11.620
No way!

14:13.290 --> 14:14.920
You know what? Never mind.
Never mind all that.

14:14.920 --> 14:18.620
[ Imitates air horn ]

14:18.620 --> 14:20.540
Boys' weekend, babyyy!

14:20.540 --> 14:21.330
[ Laughing ]

14:21.330 --> 14:22.120
[ Imitates air horn ]

14:26.170 --> 14:28.000
Kristin: Okay, guys,
let's run the cues

14:28.000 --> 14:29.670
for Act Three
one more time, please.

14:29.670 --> 14:30.750
Oh, hi!

14:30.750 --> 14:32.540
You guys are lifesavers.

14:32.540 --> 14:34.120
The kids are really working
their tails off.

14:34.120 --> 14:37.210
Oh, well, this is Amy's idea.
And she paid for it.

14:37.210 --> 14:40.250
But, um,
I carried more boxes.

14:40.250 --> 14:42.330
[ Laughs ]

14:42.330 --> 14:44.170
I'm really sorry
to hear about your mom.

14:44.170 --> 14:45.540
Thank you.

14:45.540 --> 14:48.420
Yeah, yeah, it's, um,
it's been an adjustment.

14:48.420 --> 14:51.380
And the play has been
a-a welcome distraction.

14:51.380 --> 14:53.830
Reese has been
an incredible help.

14:53.830 --> 14:56.000
Our Reese?
Yeah.

14:56.000 --> 14:58.250
She -- She designed the sets
and the poster

14:58.250 --> 15:01.460
and -- and she's basically been
our de facto stage manager.

15:01.460 --> 15:03.330
Uh, hey, Cameron,
can you hold that stardrop?

15:03.330 --> 15:06.750
We need to reset
for Act Three.

15:06.750 --> 15:09.080
You two better get here early
and snag the best seats.

15:09.080 --> 15:11.210
Yeah. We'll get here
super early.

15:11.210 --> 15:14.380
Uh, but I...have
got to get going.

15:14.380 --> 15:15.830
So, um...

15:15.830 --> 15:17.880
-Okay, bye.
-See you later.

15:17.880 --> 15:20.790
Uh, are you available
to chaperone

15:20.790 --> 15:22.290
the cast and crew
party tonight?

15:22.290 --> 15:25.330
[ Sighs ] I wish I could,
but I have plans.

15:25.330 --> 15:27.250
A date, actually.

15:27.250 --> 15:30.170
That is so great.
[ Giggles ]

15:30.170 --> 15:32.460
Well, hey, you're -- you're
welcome to bring him.

15:32.460 --> 15:34.750
Yeah. Well, that sounds
much more enjoyable

15:34.750 --> 15:38.250
than mini-golf, which
I inexplicably suggested.

15:38.250 --> 15:39.790
It's a disaster
waiting to happen.

15:39.790 --> 15:41.000
Seriously, I don't know
what to do,

15:41.000 --> 15:42.620
I don't know what to say,
I don't know how to act --

15:42.620 --> 15:44.500
Amy. Amy. Amy.

15:44.500 --> 15:45.920
Let's have some pizza.

15:45.920 --> 15:47.380
[ Indistinct chatter ]

15:47.380 --> 15:49.080
I haven't been out
with anybody

15:49.080 --> 15:52.420
who wasn't my husband
in over 20 years.

15:52.420 --> 15:54.420
The experience really isn't
that much different

15:54.420 --> 15:55.830
than when you
were a teenager.

15:55.830 --> 15:58.170
My mother drove me to
the last date that I went on.

15:58.170 --> 16:00.960
Okay. Well, that's, uh...
[ Laughs ]

16:00.960 --> 16:02.460
Yeah, but, you know,
the good news is

16:02.460 --> 16:04.330
you've already got the toughest
part out of the way.

16:04.330 --> 16:05.790
Now you just get
to know each other

16:05.790 --> 16:07.540
and see if you're
compatible.

16:07.540 --> 16:12.080
"Hi. I'm a widowed mother
of a teenage daughter.

16:12.080 --> 16:14.330
I like good books
and long walks on the beach

16:14.330 --> 16:16.120
when I'm not being
driven insane by my twin brother

16:16.120 --> 16:17.830
who, oh, by the way,
he also lives with me."

16:17.830 --> 16:19.920
I'm sure this Iggy guy
has issues of his own.

16:19.920 --> 16:21.540
Right? 'Cause everyone
has baggage.

16:21.540 --> 16:24.750
You just -- You don't unpack it
all on the first night.

16:24.750 --> 16:27.710
Yeah. Okay, but what if
I start to unpack?

16:27.710 --> 16:30.620
Uh, then focus on
the mini-golf, right?

16:30.620 --> 16:32.120
Yeah.
Destroy him if you have to.

16:32.120 --> 16:33.710
Mm-hmm.
Wait. Hold that thought.

16:33.710 --> 16:35.710
Uh, Jeffery, Marcella.

16:35.710 --> 16:38.330
Yeah, please keep your hands
and your mouths to yourselves.

16:38.330 --> 16:42.670
[ Rumbling ]

16:42.670 --> 16:44.540
Ava: Do you ever have
the urge to take a big bite

16:44.540 --> 16:47.460
out of one of those?

16:47.460 --> 16:51.790
I think it must be the color.
Or the swirls.

16:51.790 --> 16:53.790
Reminds me of taffy.

16:53.790 --> 16:55.250
Thanks for coming, Ava.

16:55.250 --> 16:57.420
Surprised to get
the invitation.

16:58.920 --> 17:01.790
I'm supposed to be
taking some time off.

17:06.420 --> 17:08.170
But I really need
to discuss Dave.

17:08.170 --> 17:10.170
Oh, boy.
What about him?

17:10.170 --> 17:12.540
Have you seen him
recently?

17:16.620 --> 17:17.920
Sure.

17:17.920 --> 17:18.830
You have?

17:18.830 --> 17:21.580
Last night, in a dream.

17:21.580 --> 17:23.290
You were there, too.

17:23.290 --> 17:25.710
And there were
so many puppies.

17:25.710 --> 17:27.540
Have you seen Dave somewhere
that wasn't a dream?

17:27.540 --> 17:29.790
No.

17:29.790 --> 17:31.920
That's what I thought.

17:33.380 --> 17:34.420
[ Pins clatter ]

17:34.420 --> 17:36.170
Are you looking for him?

17:36.170 --> 17:39.210
More like
looking into him.

17:39.210 --> 17:42.210
He showed up last week,
offering to help with Kevin,

17:42.210 --> 17:44.620
but something's
felt off ever since.

17:44.620 --> 17:47.080
Well, yeah.
There's a reason for that.

17:47.080 --> 17:50.710
Dave's the one who told the rest
of us not to listen to you.

17:50.710 --> 17:51.670
He was?

17:51.670 --> 17:54.290
You bet.
Right after we got here.

17:54.290 --> 17:57.920
Very angry,
and very convincing.

17:57.920 --> 17:59.460
[ Giggles ]

17:59.460 --> 18:02.420
This game
is really easy.

18:02.420 --> 18:04.580
S-so, what do you
think he's up to?

18:06.460 --> 18:10.330
I don't know,
but I am gonna find out.

18:11.380 --> 18:14.210
And then
I'll make him cry.

18:15.830 --> 18:17.290
[ Pins clatter ]

18:17.290 --> 18:18.420
-[ Sighs ]
-Uh, I think I need

18:18.420 --> 18:19.750
one more painting
from the house.

18:19.750 --> 18:22.540
I'll be right back.
Okay.

18:22.540 --> 18:24.040
[ Door opens ]

18:24.040 --> 18:28.120
What's wrong?
Talk to Dave.

18:28.120 --> 18:30.710
You should have seen
Reese on that stage.

18:30.710 --> 18:32.210
It was like
a different kid.

18:32.210 --> 18:35.000
No moping, no sarcasm.
She was engaged.

18:35.000 --> 18:36.830
Her hair was
in a ponytail, Dave.

18:36.830 --> 18:38.790
Yeah, nothin' says confidence
like a strong pony,

18:38.790 --> 18:40.750
that's for sure.

18:40.750 --> 18:44.170
And now I'm the knob
who's bailing on his niece.

18:44.170 --> 18:45.380
Yet again.

18:45.380 --> 18:47.500
Hey. Kev.

18:47.500 --> 18:48.920
You're not a knob.

18:48.920 --> 18:51.000
Tell that to Reese
after I don't show up tonight.

18:51.000 --> 18:51.880
Well, then go to the play.

18:51.880 --> 18:54.880
And do what? Ditch Ethan?

18:54.880 --> 18:56.960
Yeah, you're in a tough spot,
amigo. No doubt.

18:56.960 --> 18:59.670
Yeah.
But even a non-human

18:59.670 --> 19:02.670
like myself can tell
that family is a key component

19:02.670 --> 19:04.420
to your spiritual
well-being.

19:04.420 --> 19:07.500
And, in that this entire
shebang is all about

19:07.500 --> 19:10.460
strengthening your spirit,
isn't it entirely possible

19:10.460 --> 19:14.880
that supporting Reese is
the better decision right now,

19:14.880 --> 19:16.580
I mean, you know,
spiritually?

19:16.580 --> 19:19.170
Yeah. That sounds smart.

19:20.790 --> 19:23.040
Because it is.
[ Laughs ]

19:25.380 --> 19:28.500
Listen, um, Kev,
the Universe has asked

19:28.500 --> 19:30.830
far too much of you,
and that sucks.

19:30.830 --> 19:34.000
So, I'm stepping up.

19:34.000 --> 19:35.960
Time for the rubber
to meet the road.

19:35.960 --> 19:38.620
Team Kevin's got your back,
muchacho.

19:38.620 --> 19:42.750
Hi! Hi, I'm a good friend of
Kevin's. My name is Dave.

19:42.750 --> 19:45.330
Um, nice to meet you, Dave.
I'm Ethan.

19:45.330 --> 19:49.000
Bad news -- uh, Kevin
can't make it to Austin.

19:49.000 --> 19:50.330
He has a family emergency.

19:50.330 --> 19:52.000
But I can, you know, I mean,

19:52.000 --> 19:53.120
if that's cool with you,
of course.

19:53.120 --> 19:55.080
Um, yeah, I-I guess.

19:55.080 --> 19:56.710
I'm a huge art buff.

19:56.710 --> 19:58.750
I checked out a bunch
of your stuff in the truck --

19:58.750 --> 20:00.040
really evocative stuff, man.

20:00.040 --> 20:00.830
Trè bien.

20:00.830 --> 20:02.620
Uh -- Uh, thanks.

20:02.620 --> 20:05.040
Now, correct me if I'm wrong,
but do I sense a slight

20:05.040 --> 20:07.290
undertone of Fauvism
in much of your oil work?

20:07.290 --> 20:09.790
No, you're right.
Um, I'm always drawn

20:09.790 --> 20:11.620
to intense usage of --
of color.

20:11.620 --> 20:13.420
Ethan, you can see
this guy?

20:13.420 --> 20:14.790
Um, y-yeah.

20:14.790 --> 20:17.120
Yeah, of course he can...
see me, Kevin.

20:17.120 --> 20:18.460
Why wouldn't he
be able to see me?

20:18.460 --> 20:20.500
Hey, good thing I'm driving
you to Austin, huh?

20:20.500 --> 20:22.670
[ Laughs ] Come on.

20:22.670 --> 20:25.500
♪♪

20:31.210 --> 20:32.290
-What the hell, Dave?
-Apologies, Kevin.

20:32.290 --> 20:33.620
I did not mean
to overstep my bounds.

20:33.620 --> 20:34.880
I was just trying to help.
No, no!

20:34.880 --> 20:36.880
Since when can you reveal
yourself to other people?

20:36.880 --> 20:39.920
Since...forever.

20:39.920 --> 20:43.120
I -- I thought you guys
couldn't show yourselves

20:43.120 --> 20:44.540
to other humans?

20:44.540 --> 20:46.580
[ Laughs ]

20:46.580 --> 20:49.040
Who the heck
told ya th-- Oh.

20:51.750 --> 20:53.210
Why would she lie to me?

20:53.210 --> 20:56.580
Kev, we both know Yvette
isn't exactly the sharing type,

20:56.580 --> 20:59.170
but I'm sure
she had her reasons.

20:59.170 --> 21:01.380
What else hasn't
she told me about?

21:01.380 --> 21:02.670
I want to know.

21:02.670 --> 21:05.380
Bud, if it were up to me,
I'd tell you everything.

21:05.380 --> 21:06.920
Honesty is kind of
my number-one jam.

21:06.920 --> 21:09.420
But just when Yvette gets back,
have a chat with her,

21:09.420 --> 21:11.580
clear the air.
Awesome.

21:11.580 --> 21:14.040
Now quit being such a downer
and go hang with your family.

21:14.040 --> 21:15.710
Dave's got this
"Universe" junk handled.

21:15.710 --> 21:17.000
Enjoy the night off.

21:17.000 --> 21:18.750
Thanks, Dave.
Okay.

21:20.790 --> 21:23.290
♪♪

21:23.290 --> 21:24.830
No, thank you,
uh, ma'am, for that.

21:24.830 --> 21:27.250
So, you know, if you just take
your seats and enjoy the play.

21:27.250 --> 21:28.920
Okay, that's great.

21:28.920 --> 21:30.330
[ Exhales sharply ]

21:30.330 --> 21:31.540
Hey.
Hi.

21:31.540 --> 21:32.620
You seem a little bit
overwhelmed.

21:32.620 --> 21:34.750
Uh, yeah.
Well, you know, let's see.

21:34.750 --> 21:37.040
Um, the fog machine still
isn't working,

21:37.040 --> 21:38.620
and the cast decided
they need a different

21:38.620 --> 21:40.210
flavor of seltzer
because they heard

21:40.210 --> 21:41.460
that Lin-Manuel
drinks pamplemousse,

21:41.460 --> 21:44.380
so [laughs] that was --
anyway, enough about --

21:44.380 --> 21:46.290
How are you? Are you feeling
better about the date?

21:46.290 --> 21:49.000
More so than I did this morning,
thanks to you, so thank you.

21:49.000 --> 21:50.880
It's gonna be fine.

21:50.880 --> 21:54.210
Excuse me, I heard there were
programs over here.

21:54.210 --> 21:55.790
Deputy, nice of you
to join us.

21:55.790 --> 21:57.080
Thank you.

21:57.080 --> 21:58.960
Well, uh, this is
a bit of a surprise.

21:58.960 --> 22:00.920
Yeah, is it, uh, strange
for a grown man

22:00.920 --> 22:02.670
to be watching
a high-school play?

22:02.670 --> 22:03.920
Uh, yeah, kind of.

22:03.920 --> 22:05.580
[ Chuckling ]

22:05.580 --> 22:07.500
Well, the, uh, Chief's daughter
is one of the leads.

22:07.500 --> 22:09.750
Our attendance tonight
was "recommended."

22:09.750 --> 22:12.960
[ Scoffs ]

22:12.960 --> 22:15.580
So, um, do you want to go get
something to eat afterwards?

22:15.580 --> 22:16.880
We can't!

22:16.880 --> 22:20.290
Yeah. Uh, we -- we can't,
because, um, we're stuck

22:20.290 --> 22:22.750
chaperoning the cast and crew
after party,

22:22.750 --> 22:24.710
so we're just stuck doing that
all night long,

22:24.710 --> 22:27.080
so chaperoning away, right?
Yep!

22:27.080 --> 22:29.080
Okay, well, um,
good luck with all that.

22:29.080 --> 22:31.040
Thank you.
Yeah!

22:31.040 --> 22:32.420
That was fine, right?
Well, it -- it --

22:32.420 --> 22:34.880
It sounded fine. Yes.
It was fine.

22:34.880 --> 22:38.380
Woman: Please take your seats.
The show will begin shortly.

22:38.380 --> 22:40.420
[ Indistinct conversations ]

22:40.420 --> 22:43.080
♪♪

22:43.080 --> 22:44.500
[ Clattering in distance ]

22:44.500 --> 22:46.670
Kevin: Ow!

22:46.670 --> 22:50.620
♪♪

22:50.620 --> 22:55.500
[ Door closes ]

22:55.500 --> 23:01.580
Thus die I, thus, thus...

23:01.580 --> 23:02.880
[ Sighs ]

23:02.880 --> 23:06.330
Now die, die, die.

23:06.330 --> 23:12.670
[ Applause ]

23:12.670 --> 23:14.880
Kevin: Whoo!

23:14.880 --> 23:15.960
-[ Hushed ] Stop it.
-Reese!

23:15.960 --> 23:17.540
Move that set!

23:17.540 --> 23:19.460
Seamless transition!

23:19.460 --> 23:21.920
Nice and smooth! Whoo!

23:21.920 --> 23:24.120
Asleep, my love?

23:24.120 --> 23:26.210
What, dead, my dove?

23:26.210 --> 23:27.790
O Pyramus, arise.

23:27.790 --> 23:29.170
We need to talk now.

23:29.170 --> 23:31.330
Speak, speak.
Quite dumb?

23:31.330 --> 23:32.710
Now, Kevin.
We need to talk now.

23:32.710 --> 23:34.000
Dead -- a tomb must
cover thy sweet --

23:34.000 --> 23:36.000
You're ignoring me?

23:36.000 --> 23:40.670
I know you can
hear me, Kevin!

23:40.670 --> 23:42.670
You want to sit here
and act the fool all night?

23:42.670 --> 23:46.670
Okay. You just
sit there and watch.

23:46.670 --> 23:48.880
With hands as pale as milk --
lay them in gore --

23:48.880 --> 23:50.250
Kevin, cool it, man.

23:50.250 --> 23:51.380
Sorry, sorry.

23:51.380 --> 23:53.620
With shears
of his threaded silk.

23:53.620 --> 23:58.330
How's this, Kevin?
Can you see me now?

23:58.330 --> 24:01.580
Just a private little show --
me and you.

24:01.580 --> 24:04.500
[ Clears throat ]
I have to pee.

24:04.500 --> 24:07.420
What the hell
is wrong with you?

24:07.420 --> 24:10.670
Me? Nothing's wrong with me.
I feel wonderful.

24:10.670 --> 24:13.670
Oh! I'm glad, because while
you've been goofing off,

24:13.670 --> 24:16.830
Dave has been working against us
this entire time.

24:16.830 --> 24:18.500
We can't trust him.

24:18.500 --> 24:19.880
Ha!

24:19.880 --> 24:21.880
[ Laughs ] Wow.

24:21.880 --> 24:23.920
Whoo, boy. Amazing.

24:23.920 --> 24:25.330
This isn't funny, Kevin.

24:25.330 --> 24:27.000
This is hilarious.
This is about, um,

24:27.000 --> 24:30.960
as funny as it [laughs] gets --
you talking to me about trust.

24:30.960 --> 24:32.620
What are you
carrying on about?

24:32.620 --> 24:33.960
Oh, well, um...

24:33.960 --> 24:36.670
[ Hushed ] I know you can reveal
yourself to other people.

24:39.120 --> 24:40.290
[ Normal voice ] Surprise!

24:40.290 --> 24:44.000
So please, please, please
continue to lecture me

24:44.000 --> 24:48.000
about the importance
of trust and honesty.

24:48.000 --> 24:53.210
We didn't know who or what

24:53.210 --> 24:54.580
affected the other
righteous,

24:54.580 --> 24:58.460
so drawing attention to you
by parading around

24:58.460 --> 25:02.710
and revealing myself felt like
a pretty foolish strategy.

25:02.710 --> 25:06.460
Really? Um, because from --
from where I --

25:06.460 --> 25:09.580
from where I stand, it felt like
you could've spared me --

25:09.580 --> 25:12.120
and Amy and Reese --
from a huge amount of trouble,

25:12.120 --> 25:14.580
but you chose not to.

25:14.580 --> 25:18.420
I've been gone one day, and now
you don't trust me anymore?

25:18.420 --> 25:20.830
[ Chuckles ]

25:20.830 --> 25:22.880
It's a funny thing
about us humans.

25:22.880 --> 25:25.670
We find it hard to
trust people when they lie.

25:25.670 --> 25:28.620
♪♪

25:28.620 --> 25:31.040
Dave is manipulating you,
Kevin.

25:31.040 --> 25:33.290
Dave? What about you?

25:33.290 --> 25:34.620
The only thing Dave's
ever done is help.

25:34.620 --> 25:36.040
So is that why you're
not with Ethan,

25:36.040 --> 25:37.500
because Dave
is helping you?

25:37.500 --> 25:39.960
Yeah, yeah, actually.
And you know why?

25:39.960 --> 25:41.580
Because we -- we work
together as a team.

25:41.580 --> 25:42.750
[ Scoffs ] I'm sure.

25:42.750 --> 25:44.380
And you know what?
Now that I think about it,

25:44.380 --> 25:47.960
um, maybe it's time that
I consider a -- a lineup change.

25:49.710 --> 25:53.420
Namely you on the bench.

25:53.420 --> 25:55.500
Sports.

26:00.830 --> 26:02.580
So I don't want
to intimidate you,

26:02.580 --> 26:04.830
but I did score a hole-in-one
on this course

26:04.830 --> 26:06.420
about five years ago at
Reese's birthday party.

26:06.420 --> 26:07.750
Is that so?

26:09.920 --> 26:11.250
-Hey.
-Yeah, 24 kids.

26:11.250 --> 26:13.750
Just balls
flying everywhere.

26:13.750 --> 26:16.080
It was...
Wow. [Laughs] Okay.

26:16.080 --> 26:18.790
That actually sounded a lot
more porny than I intended.

26:18.790 --> 26:20.540
[ Indistinct chatter ]

26:20.540 --> 26:23.960
♪♪

26:23.960 --> 26:25.580
-Wow.
-[ Laughs ]

26:25.580 --> 26:28.170
So, uh, how you
feeling right now?

26:28.170 --> 26:31.540
I'm feeling like you're
three strokes behind, mister.

26:31.540 --> 26:34.120
Well, I -- I-I just --
I wasn't sure

26:34.120 --> 26:38.380
if all of this was a bit weird
for you, you know.

26:38.380 --> 26:41.880
It's a little different,
but I'm having fun.

26:41.880 --> 26:43.500
I took two showers today.

26:43.500 --> 26:44.460
I'm sorry?

26:44.460 --> 26:45.670
Yeah, I was
getting ready earlier,

26:45.670 --> 26:48.620
and I took a shower,
and then I second guessed

26:48.620 --> 26:50.000
the amount
of cologne I put on.

26:50.000 --> 26:52.380
Uh, well,
that is fascinating.

26:52.380 --> 26:55.500
Which is to say that if
I was nervous for tonight,

26:55.500 --> 26:57.920
[laughs] I can imagine,
you know, the prospect

26:57.920 --> 27:01.420
of our date holding
a little more anxiety for you.

27:01.420 --> 27:02.620
Okay.

27:02.620 --> 27:05.330
Maybe I was a little bit
nervous about tonight.

27:05.330 --> 27:07.420
[ Laughs ]

27:07.420 --> 27:10.500
I just -- I didn't know
if it would feel strange

27:10.500 --> 27:13.380
being on a date
with somebody that wasn't Jon,

27:13.380 --> 27:14.750
and I'd feel like I was
cheating on him.

27:14.750 --> 27:16.710
Can you even cheat
on a dead person?

27:16.710 --> 27:18.670
Am I a bad kisser
and he never told me about it?

27:18.670 --> 27:20.790
I mean, what other quirks
was he hiding from me?

27:20.790 --> 27:23.710
Do I snore? Do I chew loudly?
Do I have an oddly shaped head?

27:23.710 --> 27:26.000
Do my clothes have this,
like, funky, weird mildew smell

27:26.000 --> 27:29.290
that I just don't notice
but you would definitely notice?

27:29.290 --> 27:31.620
[ Music plays indistinctly ]

27:31.620 --> 27:36.170
Dave? Dave!

27:36.170 --> 27:37.250
Dave!!

27:37.250 --> 27:38.120
I'm Dave.
Yep.

27:38.120 --> 27:38.920
What?
Hey.

27:38.920 --> 27:40.420
Hey!
Hi.

27:40.420 --> 27:41.670
Hey, man. How's it going?
How was the show?

27:41.670 --> 27:43.670
Shouldn't you be
in Austin?

27:43.670 --> 27:45.000
No.

27:45.000 --> 27:46.380
Oh, my goodness,
what a bust.

27:46.380 --> 27:48.040
That guy does not
have the confidence

27:48.040 --> 27:49.460
to become an artist.

27:49.460 --> 27:53.170
That's...sort of
the entire reason

27:53.170 --> 27:54.960
we were helping Ethan
in the first place, buddy?

27:54.960 --> 27:55.960
I'm not
a miracle worker.

27:55.960 --> 27:57.000
[ Can top pops ]
I-I don't understand.

27:57.000 --> 27:58.120
What -- What happened?

27:58.120 --> 28:00.420
Mm. [ Laughs, sniffs ]

28:00.420 --> 28:02.040
Nothing.

28:02.040 --> 28:03.540
The guy froze -- literally.

28:03.540 --> 28:05.210
He would not
leave the truck.

28:05.210 --> 28:06.620
Well, what did you do?

28:06.620 --> 28:08.460
What was I supposed to do,
kick him out of the truck?

28:08.460 --> 28:09.830
Yeah.

28:09.830 --> 28:11.960
But with your words, maybe.

28:11.960 --> 28:13.580
With my...? [ Laughs ]

28:13.580 --> 28:15.330
Okay. No.
Kev, bro, look.

28:15.330 --> 28:17.540
You're talking to
a "Free Will" guy here, okay?

28:17.540 --> 28:18.920
I had to respect
the man's wishes.

28:18.920 --> 28:20.290
No --
So, no -- You know,

28:20.290 --> 28:22.210
we just went and got
some wings and headed home

28:22.210 --> 28:23.210
and called it a night.
Oh, my...

28:23.210 --> 28:24.540
We'll get 'em
next time, tiger.

28:24.540 --> 28:25.920
Ah!

28:25.920 --> 28:27.250
I knew it. I knew it.

28:27.250 --> 28:28.880
I-I-I -- I shouldn't
have gone to the show.

28:28.880 --> 28:30.500
I should've trusted my gut.

28:30.500 --> 28:32.710
Yvette never would have let me
blow off the mission like that.

28:32.710 --> 28:34.710
Ouch.
I'm sitting right here.

28:34.710 --> 28:38.000
If I had just stayed with Ethan,
everything would be fine.

28:38.000 --> 28:41.670
I put Yvette on the bench
for you, Dave.

28:41.670 --> 28:42.670
Follow me.

28:42.670 --> 28:43.750
What? Wha--

28:43.750 --> 28:46.170
Eh -- Come on.

28:46.170 --> 28:48.830
Did I just spend
the last two hours

28:48.830 --> 28:50.710
talking about
myself nonstop?

28:50.710 --> 28:53.710
More like an hour 45.

28:53.710 --> 28:57.500
Okay, well, let me please
start by apologizing

28:57.500 --> 29:00.250
for turning our date
into a therapy session.

29:00.250 --> 29:02.580
Well, to be fair, I mean,
I am the one that started us

29:02.580 --> 29:03.830
down that path so...

29:03.830 --> 29:05.120
So it's your fault.

29:05.120 --> 29:06.960
I mean, anything
to keep you from seeing

29:06.960 --> 29:08.580
how terrible I am
at mini golf.

29:08.580 --> 29:11.290
Oh, I noticed that,
like, immediately.

29:11.290 --> 29:12.880
[ Laughs ] Did you?
Yeah, right off...

29:12.880 --> 29:14.460
Gah!
Right away.

29:14.460 --> 29:17.120
[ Both laugh ]

29:17.120 --> 29:19.210
Okay, well, at least
you know everything

29:19.210 --> 29:20.330
there is to know about me.

29:20.330 --> 29:23.460
[ Scoffs ]
I very much doubt that.

29:23.460 --> 29:27.170
Okay, well,
my hang-ups at least.

29:27.170 --> 29:31.460
Well, to put it another way,
uh, you know, now that

29:31.460 --> 29:36.080
you've given voice
to these anxieties,

29:36.080 --> 29:40.670
you don't have to worry about it
on a second date.

29:40.670 --> 29:43.000
A second date?
[ Chuckles ]

29:44.920 --> 29:46.790
Do me a favor and stand
right there for a second.

29:46.790 --> 29:48.540
Time for your lesson.

29:48.540 --> 29:53.120
Can you tell me what color
paint is in this can?

29:53.120 --> 29:55.040
I-I don't know.
Fair enough.

29:55.040 --> 29:56.540
I, however, do know
what color paint

29:56.540 --> 30:00.080
is inside of this can,
and that color...

30:00.080 --> 30:01.080
is red.

30:01.080 --> 30:03.750
[ Lid clatters ]

30:03.750 --> 30:05.080
What the heck?!

30:05.080 --> 30:07.080
Oh, my goodness.
[ Laughing ] I am so sorry.

30:07.080 --> 30:08.670
I'm sorry about that.
What a booboo.

30:08.670 --> 30:09.830
Okay, just a sec.

30:09.830 --> 30:11.790
This was my only nice shirt.

30:11.790 --> 30:13.500
Eh, don't worry about it.

30:13.500 --> 30:14.670
I got it.

30:14.670 --> 30:17.210
The paint inside
of this can is green.

30:17.210 --> 30:18.750
Okay, don't!
Please don't, please don't!

30:18.750 --> 30:20.830
Okay? I get it.

30:20.830 --> 30:22.670
All right?

30:22.670 --> 30:24.000
Enough! Okay?

30:24.000 --> 30:26.000
Enough. Stop it.

30:27.290 --> 30:28.290
[ Sighs ]

30:28.290 --> 30:30.000
And...scene.

30:30.000 --> 30:31.830
Now, here's the part where
I drop some knowledge.

30:31.830 --> 30:33.080
Does it involve
dry-cleaning?

30:33.080 --> 30:34.500
Very good.

30:34.500 --> 30:36.500
Kevin, my existence
as a warrior for God is,

30:36.500 --> 30:38.790
to put it mildly,
pretty sweet,

30:38.790 --> 30:41.750
but there are still many things
with regard to my "warriordom"

30:41.750 --> 30:42.880
that I do not know.

30:42.880 --> 30:44.170
Yeah, I'm picking up
on that.

30:44.170 --> 30:47.040
Yvette and I,
we're the same.

30:47.040 --> 30:49.960
We have the same capabilities,
the same limitations.

30:49.960 --> 30:51.920
There is one difference,
however.

30:51.920 --> 30:55.080
I am able to admit
when I've made a mistake.

30:57.750 --> 30:59.920
Yvette, on the other hand,
God love her,

30:59.920 --> 31:01.880
she just can't help but act like
she has all the answers

31:01.880 --> 31:03.580
even when she's wrong.

31:03.580 --> 31:06.250
But, Kevin, here's the point --
no one is infallible,

31:06.250 --> 31:10.250
not even beings like us,
no matter what she says.

31:10.250 --> 31:12.000
Yvette: Hey!

31:13.120 --> 31:15.040
-Oh, boy.
-I'm not here for you.

31:15.040 --> 31:17.080
Got business
with this jackass.

31:22.040 --> 31:23.580
-Sidebar. Now.
-No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

31:23.580 --> 31:25.170
No sidebars, no disappearing,
no magic doors,

31:25.170 --> 31:26.620
just no more secrets.

31:26.620 --> 31:28.750
Kevin, I don't know what
he's been telling you, but --

31:28.750 --> 31:30.380
Only the truth,
sweetheart.

31:30.380 --> 31:31.290
You should give it
a whirl sometime.

31:31.290 --> 31:34.250
Ooh, that's big talk
coming from a guy who's been

31:34.250 --> 31:38.460
slithering behind my back
since you landed on this planet.

31:38.460 --> 31:41.290
Now, does your truth
include an explanation

31:41.290 --> 31:43.790
of why you've been
working against us?

31:43.790 --> 31:47.120
No. No, no, no.
Not us. You.

31:47.120 --> 31:49.710
Kevin, do you know why we
followed Yvette down here.

31:49.710 --> 31:51.040
No, I don't.

31:51.040 --> 31:52.540
We followed her because

31:52.540 --> 31:55.500
she told us she could
fix everything.

31:55.500 --> 31:58.960
She told God, she told
anyone who would listen,

31:58.960 --> 32:00.420
and we believed her.

32:00.420 --> 32:03.250
We left our home,
only to get here and realize

32:03.250 --> 32:05.790
that her entire plan
was worthless.

32:05.790 --> 32:07.380
She was just making it up
as she went along.

32:07.380 --> 32:10.210
You knew exactly what
you signed up for, Dave.

32:10.210 --> 32:13.290
I I signed up because
I believed in you --

32:13.290 --> 32:15.540
so confident, so sure
that you could

32:15.540 --> 32:18.920
protect the righteous
and save humanity.

32:18.920 --> 32:20.460
She's saying you'll find
a whole new generation

32:20.460 --> 32:23.710
of the righteous when
the truth is she has no idea.

32:23.710 --> 32:25.830
You want to know
what I think?

32:25.830 --> 32:27.670
I think
there aren't any more.

32:27.670 --> 32:30.080
And I think
there won't be anymore.

32:31.830 --> 32:34.500
So, which one of us
is right?

32:34.500 --> 32:36.120
Go on. Tell him.

32:39.170 --> 32:42.460
I don't know.

32:42.460 --> 32:44.670
Boom.
Told you.

32:44.670 --> 32:46.330
Uh, Dave, please.

32:46.330 --> 32:48.710
But...

32:48.710 --> 32:50.330
[ Sighs ]

32:50.330 --> 32:52.290
That doesn't mean
Dave's correct.

32:52.290 --> 32:55.710
You must understand
this was never about

32:55.710 --> 32:57.580
certainty for me.

32:57.580 --> 33:02.000
It has been
and always will be

33:02.000 --> 33:07.040
about my faith in you.

33:07.040 --> 33:12.580
I believe that there's
no one on this planet

33:12.580 --> 33:15.000
who can accomplish
what you can.

33:15.000 --> 33:18.330
Not me, not Dave.

33:18.330 --> 33:20.830
You.

33:20.830 --> 33:22.210
Dave: Goose bumps.

33:22.210 --> 33:24.330
Yeah, I forgot how good
you were at the faith bit.

33:25.290 --> 33:27.250
What is it
that you want, Dave?

33:27.250 --> 33:30.420
I want Kevin to wake up
and realize

33:30.420 --> 33:33.670
that he's a "Plan B,"
that he's an audible.

33:33.670 --> 33:35.670
I want him to think about
all the rinky-dink tasks

33:35.670 --> 33:38.210
he kills himself for
a-and whether the future

33:38.210 --> 33:41.920
of the Universe hinge's on
some dude's art show.

33:41.920 --> 33:46.170
Because if he still thinks
that you've got the answers...

33:46.170 --> 33:49.880
then he's stranded...

33:49.880 --> 33:52.420
with no way home.

33:52.420 --> 33:57.210
♪♪

33:57.210 --> 34:00.040
[ Sighs ] I, uh...

34:00.040 --> 34:03.120
Um...

34:03.120 --> 34:06.210
I'm gonna g-go to bed.

34:06.210 --> 34:11.170
♪♪

34:11.170 --> 34:14.420
[ Birds singing,
knock on door ]

34:14.420 --> 34:15.920
Hi, Ms. Allen.

34:15.920 --> 34:18.210
Reese. Just the person
I was hoping to see.

34:18.210 --> 34:20.500
Uh, this is for you.

34:20.500 --> 34:22.250
Oh.

34:22.250 --> 34:24.620
-Honey, who is it?
-Hey.

34:24.620 --> 34:27.500
Just brought Reese a little gift
to say thank you

34:27.500 --> 34:29.620
for being such a phenomenal
help with the play.

34:29.620 --> 34:31.290
Aww.

34:31.290 --> 34:32.880
A rock.

34:32.880 --> 34:34.670
Uh... [Chuckles]
Uh, cool.

34:34.670 --> 34:36.080
I made this.

34:36.080 --> 34:37.380
I mean, I figured
you couldn't put

34:37.380 --> 34:40.210
an entire backdrop
in your room so...

34:40.210 --> 34:41.420
Yeah.
Rock.

34:41.420 --> 34:42.750
Rock.

34:42.750 --> 34:44.460
It's -- It's really great.
Thank you.

34:44.460 --> 34:47.420
Thank you.

34:47.420 --> 34:50.120
I probably could have given
that to Reese on Monday,

34:50.120 --> 34:52.290
but I was curious
how your evening went.

34:52.290 --> 34:54.210
Yes. Yes, yes,
yes, yes, yes.

34:54.210 --> 34:57.790
[ Inhales deeply ]
So, um, well,

34:57.790 --> 35:00.670
I did not unpack all of
my baggage, for starters.

35:00.670 --> 35:01.960
Congratulations.

35:01.960 --> 35:04.710
Yeah, no, I, um,
actually opened the bag,

35:04.710 --> 35:09.170
and then I dumped the mess
all over the ground.

35:09.170 --> 35:10.710
Okay. Well, that's --
that's a different --

35:10.710 --> 35:13.460
that's a different
way to go about things.

35:13.460 --> 35:16.580
But he seems interested
in a second date, I think.

35:16.580 --> 35:17.830
Well, that's great!
Yeah.

35:17.830 --> 35:19.250
[ Laughs ]

35:19.250 --> 35:21.460
What are you gonna tell
Nate this time?

35:21.460 --> 35:23.580
Yeah.
Yeah.

35:23.580 --> 35:25.250
That was really unexpected.

35:25.250 --> 35:26.540
[ Laughs ]
You're telling me.

35:26.540 --> 35:27.620
It just...

35:27.620 --> 35:28.880
It felt weird
to tell him.

35:28.880 --> 35:30.290
[ Sighs ]

35:30.290 --> 35:31.960
I don't know.

35:31.960 --> 35:34.040
Well, maybe you should
figure that out

35:34.040 --> 35:36.880
before you give
Iggy a call.

35:36.880 --> 35:38.540
[ Sighs ]

35:38.540 --> 35:44.000
♪♪

35:44.000 --> 35:46.830
What's going on?

35:46.830 --> 35:48.710
Nothing.

35:48.710 --> 35:50.960
You've been in here
all day.

35:50.960 --> 35:52.710
Are you sad?

35:52.710 --> 35:55.790
Does this look sad
to you?

35:56.460 --> 35:59.040
[ Door closes ]

35:59.040 --> 36:02.460
Want to tell me
what's going on?

36:02.460 --> 36:05.750
Honestly, I...

36:05.750 --> 36:09.750
really, really wish I could.

36:09.750 --> 36:13.620
But can't.

36:13.620 --> 36:16.500
You know, that used
to bug me,

36:16.500 --> 36:19.380
not knowing why you were always
acting so weird all the time.

36:19.380 --> 36:23.460
Yeah, I seem to remember
you stalking me,

36:23.460 --> 36:25.710
placing a tracker
on my phone.

36:25.710 --> 36:28.500
Did you ever wonder why it
doesn't bother me anymore?

36:28.500 --> 36:31.040
Mm, nope.

36:31.040 --> 36:33.750
Was just glad you stopped
being so annoying.

36:33.750 --> 36:38.960
I realized it didn't matter why
you were being weird because,

36:38.960 --> 36:41.620
when you were weird, you were
usually helping people.

36:41.620 --> 36:44.170
You know, you don't have to
keep using the word "weird."

36:44.170 --> 36:46.420
And you've helped,
like, a lot of people.

36:46.420 --> 36:47.330
[ Chuckles softly ]

36:47.330 --> 36:48.830
Like, look at me.

36:48.830 --> 36:50.420
I try not to as a rule.

36:50.420 --> 36:55.040
I'm trying to say you
helped me, genius!

36:55.040 --> 36:58.880
Without you, I probably
wouldn't have done the play.

36:58.880 --> 37:01.330
Really.

37:01.330 --> 37:04.580
[ Voice breaking ]
I owe a lot to you.

37:04.580 --> 37:06.710
And now...

37:06.710 --> 37:08.710
[ Door opens ]

37:11.790 --> 37:13.540
Now I have this rock.

37:17.830 --> 37:19.380
Is the rock a metaphor?

37:19.380 --> 37:22.540
I'm just saying
it doesn't matter why

37:22.540 --> 37:26.380
you act weird
because you use your weirdness

37:26.380 --> 37:29.580
to do good stuff.

37:29.580 --> 37:32.420
And those
little things add up.

37:34.250 --> 37:36.040
[ Sighs ]

37:38.330 --> 37:40.120
I'm not even gonna
make a joke.

37:40.120 --> 37:42.420
[ Sighs ]

37:42.420 --> 37:43.790
[ Voice breaking ]
Thank you, Reese.

37:43.790 --> 37:45.330
That was really nice.

37:45.330 --> 37:47.620
Sure.

37:50.080 --> 37:52.750
But, you know, if you
wanted to tell me

37:52.750 --> 37:57.460
how you pull off all that stuff,
I wouldn't, like, mind.

37:57.460 --> 38:01.540
Because I don't think
you're doing it alone.

38:01.540 --> 38:04.500
Someone or something
has got to be helping you.

38:07.500 --> 38:10.920
Hey, Reese.

38:10.920 --> 38:12.880
Um...

38:14.620 --> 38:17.040
When you were a baby,
I dropped you on your h-head.

38:19.710 --> 38:23.710
And not like once --
like, three or four times.

38:23.710 --> 38:25.080
[ Laughs ]

38:25.080 --> 38:27.460
I know. I know.

38:27.460 --> 38:29.670
I know.

38:29.670 --> 38:31.960
♪♪

38:39.250 --> 38:42.210
[ Upbeat classical music plays ]

38:42.210 --> 38:43.460
[ Indistinct conversations ]

38:43.460 --> 38:46.080
-These natural colors.
-Yeah.

38:46.080 --> 38:47.250
I mean, it's already
been sold, though.

38:47.250 --> 38:49.040
-Hey. My paintings.
-Excuse me.

38:49.040 --> 38:50.000
-How did...
-Yes.

38:50.000 --> 38:52.330
Hey. Hey, there. Hi.

38:52.330 --> 38:53.750
Kevin, what's going on?

38:53.750 --> 38:58.170
This is a-a local --
very local showing of your work.

38:58.170 --> 38:59.790
[ Stammering ]
I-I don't understand.

38:59.790 --> 39:01.710
I felt bad about Austin,
so I wanted to --

39:01.710 --> 39:02.790
to make it up to you.

39:02.790 --> 39:04.420
And, uh...

39:04.420 --> 39:06.920
Ethan, dear,
I have an art question.

39:06.920 --> 39:08.580
Okay, sure. Go ahead.

39:08.580 --> 39:11.040
Do you ship to New Jersey?

39:11.040 --> 39:12.420
I'm sorry?

39:12.420 --> 39:14.710
My cousin wants
a few of these paintings,

39:14.710 --> 39:17.830
but she's being a noodge
about the postage charges.

39:17.830 --> 39:21.460
Your cousin in New Jersey
wants to buy my paintings?

39:21.460 --> 39:24.080
Aren't they for sale?

39:24.080 --> 39:25.500
Um...

39:25.500 --> 39:27.290
Uh, uh, uh,
yeah, yes, yes.

39:27.290 --> 39:29.000
Um, they are.

39:29.000 --> 39:31.210
Um, you know what?
Uh, tell her that,

39:31.210 --> 39:35.000
uh, the painting price
comes with free shipping.

39:35.000 --> 39:36.580
Are you happy now, Evelyn?

39:36.580 --> 39:38.920
[ Chuckles ]

39:38.920 --> 39:42.040
Kevin, I don't...

39:42.040 --> 39:44.210
[ Sighs ] I don't know how
to thank you for this.

39:44.210 --> 39:46.000
Oh.
I know this is small,

39:46.000 --> 39:48.330
but, man, this feels great.

39:48.330 --> 39:50.960
Like I said,
I'm a patron of the arts.

39:52.750 --> 39:54.500
Let me give you something.

39:54.500 --> 39:55.880
Oh.

39:58.040 --> 39:59.620
Here you go.

39:59.620 --> 40:01.120
[ Gasps ]

40:01.120 --> 40:03.290
Ethan, this is stunning.

40:03.290 --> 40:04.790
I...

40:04.790 --> 40:11.960
♪♪

40:11.960 --> 40:13.710
[ Whispering ] Oh, my.

